          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #13\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    The adapter converts model boxes directly into LayoutRegion; negative coordinates are clamped later, but R/B can exceed image dimensions.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    Out-of-bounds model outputs can mis-tag words and produce invalid sidecar coordinates.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/layout/adapters/pp_doclayout.py:123`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/adapters/pp_doclayout.py:125`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/adapters/pp_doclayout.py:136`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Clip x1/y1/x2/y2 to image bounds.\n- [ ] Drop or log degenerate boxes after clipping.\n- [ ] Unit-test adapter post-processing with out-of-range model results.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:04:04Z",
